# OpenCode Agent Instructions

**Docs:** https://opencode.ai/docs | **Repo:** https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode

---

## Always-On Rules

### Osgrep CLI-Only (Canary)
**Use osgrep for semantic code search in CLI-only mode.** Use first for discovery; fall back to `grep`/`glob`/`Read` on timeout/failure. Do not use `osgrep mcp`.

### Knowledge Graph Entity Lookup
**For Army C2/CC2, Packaged Agile business enrichment, meeting-note enrichment, stakeholder/contact lookup, organization context, and relationship questions, check the knowledge graph first.** Primary: `C:\development\02-Kx-to-process\knowledge-base\`
- Lookup: `python scripts/query-graph.py lookup --name "Name" --type Person --top 5`
- Broad search: `python scripts/search.py "topic" --top 5`
- Fallback: `grep`/`glob`/`Read` when scripts fail
- Skills: `knowledge-graph-builder` (extraction), `knowledge-graph-maintainer` (audits)


### API Keys / Secrets Lookup
Before searching repos for API keys or service credentials, consult `C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.config\opencode\secrets-index.jsonc`. This metadata-only index contains key names, services, canonical locations, consuming repos, duplicate locations, and status notes. Never print, copy, or commit secret values.
### ClickUp Quick References
- Army C2: list `901113158142` | Personal inbox: list `3984798`
- Use directly when task clearly belongs; ask when uncertain.

### Chrome DevTools MCP
**Use `control-chrome_*` tools for browser automation.** Never use Playwright/Puppeteer/Selenium. MCP config name: `control-chrome`.

### Semantic-First Navigation
Use search tools before broad reads: osgrep → grep/glob → targeted Read. Only read full files when small or complete context needed.

### File Tool Path Format
**All paths must be absolute.** Prefer `skills\` path over legacy `skill\`. If both exist, ask user. For HTML deliverables, use fully qualified Windows backslash paths.

### File Reading Strategy
Files >50 lines: grep/glob first. Files >200 lines: targeted reads only. Stop before reading >2 files simultaneously.

---

## Reference Index (Open only when triggered)

### Slack Messaging
**Trigger:** Slack, send Slack message, Slack notification, Slack alert, Slack DM, Slack webhook.
**Action:** Use `skill_find `slack`` first. Prefer `slack-send-message` for scripted bot-token automation and `slack-messaging` for MCP-based interactive Slack workflows.

### Microsoft 365 / Outlook / Email / Calendar
**Trigger:** Outlook, email, inbox, calendar, Microsoft 365, Exchange, Graph.
**Action:** Use `skill_find` to locate and load the appropriate skill.

### Skill Discovery Preflight
**Trigger:** Finding, editing, or using skills.
**Action:** Use `skill_find "<keyword>"` first. Lazy-vault: `~/.opencode-lazy-vault`.

**Creating/updating skills — canonical tool:** use the **`skill-creator`** skill (`~/.opencode-lazy-vault/skill-creator/SKILL.md`). It is OpenCode-specific and lazy-vault-aware: the recommended default location for new skills is the active opencode-skillful lazy vault (`~/.opencode-lazy-vault`, from `~/.config/opencode-skillful/opencode-skillful.config.mjs`). Only use native always-loaded locations (`~/.config/opencode/skills/` or `~/.config/opencode/skill/`) when the user explicitly requests always-loaded skills.

**Use `skill-creator`** (`.opencode-lazy-vault/skill-creator`) for all skill creation guidance. The helper scripts (`init_skill.py`, `quick_validate.py`, `generate_openai_yaml.py`) are now bundled in the `skill-creator` skill.

**`customize-opencode` skill note:** the built-in `customize-opencode` skill lists `~/.config/opencode/skill(s)/...` to document where OpenCode *scans* for skills (both `skill/` and `skills/` are scanned). Those are *scan/detection paths, not creation defaults*. Creation defaults come from `skill-creator` above.

Always-available skills: conductor, osgrep, git-push, perplexity-search. Load with `skill_use "<name>"` (underscores, not hyphens).

