## Tool-Layer Failure Protocol (Bun is not defined)

**At session start, run one cheap file op** (e.g., glob a known file). If a file tool returns `Bun is not defined`, switch the **whole session** to PowerShell-first via the `bash` tool immediately - do NOT retry the failing tool per-call (each retry is wasted). Bun 1.3.4 IS installed; this is a runtime sandbox-init failure, not a missing install.

Cmdlet map: Read -> `Get-Content -Raw`, Write -> `Set-Content -Encoding utf8` (or verbatim here-string `@'...'@`), Edit -> `Select-String` to locate + literal `[string]::Replace()` (NOT regex `-replace`, which eats structural chars), glob -> `Get-ChildItem -Recurse`, grep -> `Select-String`.

Full runbook: `~/.config/opencode/docs/troubleshooting/tool-failure-bun-undefined.md`

### Conductor PowerShell Edit Hazards
**Trigger:** Editing files with PowerShell; structural-character edits; regex `-replace` hazards.

For Conductor Pipeline PowerShell edit hazards (parse-check limitations, content-anchored targeting, markdown-list indentation bleed, literal structural-character edits, and session-spanning date handling), see C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.config\opencode\skill\conductor-pipeline\references\powershell-edit-hazards.md.

